Prevent End Users from Sending File Attachments in Messaging for In-App and Web

Available in: Lightning Experience. View required editions 
This article applies to:	Messaging for In-App and Messaging for Web channels 
This article doesnâ€™t apply to:	Standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel

User Permissions Needed
To choose whether end-users can send file attachments: Customize Application

By default, end-users can send file attachments to agents. To prevent end-users from sending file attachments to agents:

From Setup, enter Messaging Settings and select Messaging Settings.
Click the downward arrow to the right of your messaging channel, and select Edit.
In the Attachments section, deselect Let customers send attachments to agents.
Save your changes.

title: Preventing File Attachments in Service Cloud Messaging
